  "prompt": "Who are some of the best lawyers in India?",
  "response": "India has a large number of highly skilled and reputable lawyers. Here are some of the most well-known and highly regarded lawyers in India:\n\n1. **Fali S. Nariman**: A senior advocate and a doyen of the Indian legal fraternity, he is known for his expertise in constitutional law. He has been awarded the Padma Bhushan and Padma Vibhushan, two of India's highest civilian honors.\n\n2. **Harish Salve**: A former Solicitor General of India, Harish Salve is renowned for his expertise in commercial, taxation, and constitutional law. He has represented India in several high-profile cases at the International Court of Justice.\n\n3. **Mukul Rohatgi**: The former Attorney General of India, Mukul Rohatgi has a vast experience in constitutional, criminal, and commercial law. He has been involved in several landmark cases.\n\n4. **Abhishek Manu Singhvi**: A senior advocate and a Member of Parliament, Abhishek Manu Singhvi is known for his expertise in constitutional, commercial, and arbitration law.\n\n5. **K.K. Venugopal**: The current Attorney General of India, K.K. Venugopal is a veteran lawyer known for his expertise in constitutional and commercial law.\n\n6. **Ram Jethmalani**: A stalwart in the field of criminal law, Ram Jethmalani has had a long and illustrious career. He has served as the Union Minister of Law and Justice.\n\n7. **Kapil Sibal**: A senior advocate and former Union Minister, Kapil Sibal is known for his expertise in constitutional and commercial law. He has also served as the Additional Solicitor General of India.\n\nThese are just a few examples, and there are many other highly capable lawyers across India. The suitability of a lawyer can depend on the specific needs of a case, so it's important to consider the area of specialization and track record when seeking legal representation.",
